%% Touch outcome lifecycle. Strictly enforced in
%% salesman-state::approve_touch / reject_touch / mark_touch_sent.

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Drafted: insert_touch_draft
    Drafted --> AwaitingApproval: (always — no in-between state today)

    AwaitingApproval --> Approved: salesman approve
    AwaitingApproval --> Rejected: salesman reject
    AwaitingApproval --> Suppressed: opt-out reply lands first

    Approved --> Sent: send-pending --for-real (SMTP success)
    Approved --> Failed: send-pending --for-real (SMTP error)
    Approved --> Suppressed: opt-out reply lands first
    Approved --> Bounced: bounce notification

    Sent --> [*]
    Rejected --> [*]
    Suppressed --> [*]
    Failed --> [*]
    Bounced --> [*]

    note right of Sent
        Records receipt_id (Ed25519 signature on the
        send event, chained to the previous receipt).
    end note
